When working with Pixi.js, Three.js, HuggingFace Transformers, Playwright, or Biome, use the Context7 MCP server for documentation and code examples. These libraries are not in llms-stack.mdc.

## Workflow

1. Call `resolve-library-id` first to obtain the Context7 library ID, unless the user provides one in `/org/project` format.
2. Call `query-docs` with the library ID and a specific question. Be specific: include the task, API surface, or pattern you need.
3. Limit to 3 `query-docs` calls per question. If you cannot find what you need after 3 calls, use the best information you have.

## Pre-resolved library IDs (use directly when appropriate)

| Library | Context7 ID |
|---------|-------------|
| PixiJS | /websites/pixijs_8_x |
| Three.js | /mrdoob/three.js |
| HuggingFace Transformers | /huggingface/transformers |
| Transformers.js (browser) | /huggingface/transformers.js |
| Playwright | /microsoft/playwright |
| Biome | /websites/v1_biomejs_dev |
| HTMX | /bigskysoftware/htmx |

For version-specific queries, append the version: e.g. `/microsoft/playwright/v1.58.2`.

## When to use Context7 vs. existing docs

- **Use Context7**: Pixi.js, Three.js, HuggingFace Transformers, Playwright, Biome. Also when you need version-specific or recent patterns for any library.
- **Use llms-stack-refresh**: Bun, Elysia, htmx, Prisma, Tailwind, DaisyUI (general patterns).
- **Use notes/doc-archive**: Project architecture, API contracts, builder domain, HTMX extensions, playable runtime, local AI runtime.
